{{Infobox company | name = ACube Systems Srl | logo = | type = [[privately held company|Private]] | foundation = {{Start date|2007|01}} | location_city = [[Bassano del Grappa]] | location_country = [[Italy]] | key_people = | industry = | products = [[Minimig]], [[Sam440ep]], [[Sam460ex]], [[AmigaOne|AmigaOne 500]] | revenue = |operating_income = |net_income = | num_employees = | homepage = {{URL|www.acube-systems.biz}} }} '''ACube Systems Srl''' is a company that started in January 2007 from the synergy of the Italian companies [[Alternative Holding Group Srl]], [[Soft3]] and [[Virtual Works]].<ref>http://www.intuitionbase.com/static.php?section=en_sam440ep</ref>
The three companies have been engaged in the areas of sale, distribution and engineering of [[computer hardware|hardware]] and [[software]] for mainstream systems and alternative platforms for years. They have joined their efforts in the realization of the [[Sam440ep]] platform. Then ongoing [[History of the AmigaOS 4 dispute|dispute over ownership of AmigaOS]] cast doubts about actual release of [[AmigaOS 4]] for this new hardware,<ref>{{cite news |last=Proven |first=Liam |date=May 3, 2007 |title=The trials of the Amiga continue |url=http://www.theinquirer.net/inquirer/news/1035139/the-trials-amiga-continue/ |newspaper=The Inquirer|accessdate=April 12, 2016 }}</ref> support for Sam440ep was later introduced in AmigaOS 4.1.<ref>{{cite news |last=Reimer|first=Jeremy|date=September 23, 2008 |title=It’s alive!: Ars reviews AmigaOS 4.1|url=https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2008/09/amigaos41-ars/|newspaper=Ars Technica |accessdate=April 12, 2016 }}</ref> Since November 2007 Acube Systems distributed AmigaOS 4.0 for [[Amiga]] computers with [[PowerUP (accelerator)|PowerPC CPU cards]] on behalf of [[Hyperion Entertainment]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Klaß |first=Christian |date=November 26, 2007 |title=AmigaOS 4.0 für klassische Amigas ist fertig|url=http://www.golem.de/0711/56169.html|newspaper=Golem.de |accessdate=April 12, 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=November 27, 2007 |title=AmigaOS 4.0: Modernes Betriebssystem für Uralt-Rechner|url=http://www.computerwoche.de/a/amigaos-4-0-modernes-betriebssystem-fuer-uralt-rechner,1849003|newspaper=Computerwoche |accessdate=April 12, 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Fulco|first=Ivan |date=April 4, 2011 |title=Atari, Commodore, Spectrum Che mania il vintage hi-tech|url=http://www.repubblica.it/tecnologia/2011/04/08/news/ritorno_commodore_64-14683431/|newspaper=la Repubblica.it |accessdate=April 12, 2016 }}</ref> They also built the very first Amiga redesign in hardware: the [[Minimig]]. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.acube-systems.biz/index.php?page=company |title=ACube Systems Srl company. |publisher=ACube Systems Srl |date= |accessdate=2010-01-06 }}</ref> In September 2011, Acube Systems introduced AmigaOne 500 based on [[Sam460ex]] mainboard.<ref>{{cite press release |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |url=http://www.acube-systems.biz/index.php?page=news&id=92|title=FILE N. 1: A new AmigaOne for all Amiga users|location=Bassano del Grappa, Italy |publisher=Acube Systems|date=September 19, 2011|accessdate=April 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=September 20, 2011 |title=Amiga-System mit PowerPC-SoC |url=http://www.heise.de/ct/meldung/Amiga-System-mit-PowerPC-SoC-1346596.html |newspaper=c't magazin |accessdate=April 12, 2016 }}</ref>
