{{ITU-T Home networking Recommendations}}
Recommendation '''G.9963''' is a [[home networking]] standard under development at [[ITU-T|the International Telecommunication Union standards sector, the ITU-T]].
It was begun in 2010 by [[ITU-T]] to add [[MIMO|multiple-input and multiple-output]] (known as MIMO) capabilities to the [[G.hn]] standard originally defined in Recommendation G.9960. The standard is also known as "G.hn-mimo".<ref>{{cite web |title = G.9963 (ex G.hn-MIMO) |work= ITU-T Work Programme |url= http://www.itu.int/itu-t/workprog/wp_item.aspx?isn=7726 |accessdate= July 27, 2011 }}</ref>
As part of the family of [[G.hn]] standards, G.9963 was endorsed by the HomeGrid Forum.<ref>{{cite news |title= HomeGrid Forum Endorses Draft ITU-T MIMO Specification for Extending G.hn |author= Sheila Lashford |publisher= HomeGrid Forum |url= http://www.homegridforum.org/content/pages.php?pg=news_press_releases_item&rec_id=95 |date= May 3, 2011 |accessdate= July 27, 2011 }}</ref><ref name="TOVIM14">{{cite book|author=Ben-Tovim, Erez|date=February 2014|title=ITU G.hn - Broadband Home Networking|booktitle=MIMO Power Line Communications: Narrow and Broadband Standards, EMC, and Advanced Processing|publisher=CRC Press|series=Devices, Circuits, and Systems|editor1=Berger, Lars T.|editor2= Schwager, Andreas|editor3= Pagani, Pascal |editor4=Schneider, Daniel M|chapter=12|isbn=9781466557529|url=http://www.crcnetbase.com/doi/abs/10.1201/b16540-16}}</ref>
